  "elapsed_s": 10.8,
  "sentences_input": [
    {
      "segment_idx": 0,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 0,
      "text": "The experience of working in Majdanek and Lublin and approached by the Polish man who was slowly preparing me for the escape.",
      "word_count": 22
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 1,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 0,
      "text": "I don't remember his name.",
      "word_count": 5
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 1,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 1,
      "text": "And I did not ask for a name.",
      "word_count": 8
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 1,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 2,
      "text": "He just was calling me by my first name, by the name of [?",
      "word_count": 14
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 1,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 3,
      "text": "Tadik. ?] And when I-- this was going on for about two or three weeks, until one day he told me that we can use the outside bathroom.",
      "word_count": 28
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 2,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 0,
      "text": "This-- I beg your pardon?",
      "word_count": 5
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 3,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 0,
      "text": "During this few weeks, we were-- he was explaining to me that there is possibility of escape through the-- using the outdoor-- outdoor bathroom.",
      "word_count": 24
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 3,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 1,
      "text": "And there was a very primitive [PAUSES FOR 3 SECONDS] closure-- closure with-- you had to stand on-- over opening in the ground with a few planks of wood that you had to sit down and release yourself.",
      "word_count": 38
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 3,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 2,
      "text": "But he mentioned that behind this was right there-- tracks of the railroads passing by at the same time.",
      "word_count": 19
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 3,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 3,
      "text": "And the trick was to cross-- to get through the opening in the ground and get from underneath the wire-- the barbed wire that was surrounding the encampment of this factory-- and start running toward the train that was approaching.",
      "word_count": 40
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 4,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 0,
      "text": "When we were--",
      "word_count": 3
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 5,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 0,
      "text": "Yeah.",
      "word_count": 1
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 6,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 0,
      "text": "At night, we were returning back to-- to camp.",
      "word_count": 9
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 6,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 1,
      "text": "We were brought by truck in the morning.",
      "word_count": 8
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 6,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 2,
      "text": "And at night, we were marching from the factory back to the camp.",
      "word_count": 13
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 6,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 3,
      "text": "And they were counted very carefully by the Germans if the amount of these prisoners the same as had left in the morning.",
      "word_count": 23
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 6,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 4,
      "text": "And he was explaining to me that around 4:00 in the afternoon, there is always a train passing towards the north part of the railroad tracks.",
      "word_count": 26
    }
  ],
